      <body>
        <div>
            <pb facs="#TL-0527.jpg" n="part4_p053.jpg" xml:id="img_0053" corresp="https://id.acdh.oeaw.ac.at/tillich-lectures/part4_p053.jpg"/>
            
            <p facs="#facs_53_tr_2">
               <lb facs="#facs_53_tr_2_tl_1" n="N001"/>dʼavoir lʼautre
               <lb facs="#facs_53_tr_2_tl_2" n="N002"/>-222-
               <lb facs="#facs_53_tr_2_tl_3" n="N003"/>naturalism, affirms what he denies andernies what he affirms. And this is necessarily so. One can
               <lb facs="#facs_53_tr_2_tl_4" n="N004"/>derive the normative structure of man as man from things which are LESS than manas man. And that’s
               <lb facs="#facs_53_tr_2_tl_5" n="N005"/>what Kant meant with the ontogorical imperative. Therefore he didn’t deny not only a tyrranical God,
               <lb facs="#facs_53_tr_2_tl_6" n="N006"/>but also psychological motives [such] as fear, as authority-which is not under Iriticism—and all those
               <lb facs="#facs_53_tr_2_tl_7" n="N007"/>motives which can be brought into consideration. They all produce heteronomy. The person as person
               <lb facs="#facs_53_tr_2_tl_8" n="N008"/>cannot affirm himself in its automomous integrity and validity if he doesn’t accept the conconditional
               <lb facs="#facs_53_tr_2_tl_9" n="N009"/>character of the moral imperative.
            </p>
            <p facs="#facs_53_tr_3">
               <lb facs="#facs_53_tr_3_tl_1" n="N001"/>Now I hope only one thing, that after I repeated this about twenty times during this hour,
               <lb facs="#facs_53_tr_3_tl_2" n="N002"/>you do NOT confuse, from now on, the conconditional character of the moral imperative with the uncon¬
               <lb facs="#facs_53_tr_3_tl_3" n="N003"/>ditional character OF ANY SPECIAL CONTENT. Please don't do this mistake and then say,
               <lb facs="#facs_53_tr_3_tl_4" n="N004"/>murder
               <lb facs="#facs_53_tr_3_tl_5" n="N005"/>"Now, for the primatives of South America, or somehow in the desert, there,
               <lb facs="#facs_53_tr_3_tl_6" n="N006"/>(or something
               <lb facs="#facs_53_tr_3_tl_7" n="N007"/>like that) is a very much praised deed.” This is not the point which I make here. I AccEPT that
               <lb facs="#facs_53_tr_3_tl_8" n="N008"/>with scientific limitations, to which I may come later, but in any case this relativism is a reality
            </p>
            <p facs="#facs_53_tr_1">
               <lb facs="#facs_53_tr_1_tl_1" n="N001"/>and is a reality which one feels even more, perhaps, when one comes from another culture (as I myself
               <lb facs="#facs_53_tr_1_tl_2" n="N002"/>do), the European and the America. In suite of their relatedness, there are fundamental difference
               <lb facs="#facs_53_tr_1_tl_3" n="N003"/>in theOnical contents, which one notices if one has the boundary line situation of having been a
               <lb facs="#facs_53_tr_1_tl_4" n="N004"/>refugee once upon a time. So I don't need to be LAUGHT this, with the help of all the
               <lb facs="#facs_53_tr_1_tl_5" n="N005"/>primatives of the world. [laughter] It is already given in the relationship of Americaans and Europeans,
               <lb facs="#facs_53_tr_1_tl_6" n="N006"/>who are only PART zy primities! (smiling — daughter) But it is a quite different point.
               <lb facs="#facs_53_tr_1_tl_7" n="N007"/>Monsieur, que je ne lui ai-même
               <lb facs="#facs_53_tr_1_tl_8" n="N008"/>Monsieur le Comte de lʼhonneur et de
               <lb facs="#facs_53_tr_1_tl_9" n="N009"/>dʼavoir lʼautre beaucoup
               <lb facs="#facs_53_tr_1_tl_10" n="N010"/>de lʼhonneur et très obéissant les
               <lb facs="#facs_53_tr_1_tl_11" n="N011"/>de lʼauteur sérieusement les mêmes
               <lb facs="#facs_53_tr_1_tl_12" n="N012"/>dire une
               <lb facs="#facs_53_tr_1_tl_13" n="N013"/>Monsieur
               <lb facs="#facs_53_tr_1_tl_14" n="N014"/>dʼune manière beaucoup
               <lb facs="#facs_53_tr_1_tl_15" n="N015"/>dʼune manière vous avez
               <lb facs="#facs_53_tr_1_tl_16" n="N016"/>Monsieur
               <lb facs="#facs_53_tr_1_tl_17" n="N017"/>lʼauteur dʼune
               <lb facs="#facs_53_tr_1_tl_18" n="N018"/>quʼil ne
               <lb facs="#facs_53_tr_1_tl_19" n="N019"/>Monsieur
               <lb facs="#facs_53_tr_1_tl_20" n="N020"/>décidées que je vous en avez
               <lb facs="#facs_53_tr_1_tl_21" n="N021"/>dans une lettre de
               <lb facs="#facs_53_tr_1_tl_22" n="N022"/>Votre
            </p>
            
